   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC350831b02b3d1005818c873ba02d26d2"></a>Refitting the steering tube components
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7524"> </a>The steering tube bearings are identical but in no case may their components be swapped during reassembly.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7527"> </a>Clean all contact surfaces and lubricate with the recommended grease.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7529"> </a>To fit the outer rings (8) of bearings (6) to the steering tube, use tool (D) no. 88713.1062.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7531"> </a>Proceed as follows:
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7535"> </a>heat the steering tube to 150&nbsp;°C;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7538"> </a>fit the outer rings (8) in their seats on the steering tube;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7541"> </a>fit the fixed bush (9) with threaded hole of the tool into the lower race;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7544"> </a>fit the other movable bush (10) into the upper end of the tool and drive it fully home against the upper bearing race;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7547"> </a>tighten the nut (11), and use a wrench to seat the outer rings (8) fully in the steering tube;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">- </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7550"> </a>leave the tool assembled until the steering tube has cooled down to ensure that bearings are properly seated.
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_023803376.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7555"> </a>Insert the seal (5) (with the rim facing upwards) and the inner ring (A) of the bottom bearing (6) onto the steering shaft,
            after heating it for about 10 minutes to 120°C.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7557"> </a>Insert drift (E) no.&nbsp;88713.1072 onto the steering shaft. Push the inner race (A) on the seal (5), manually pushing for at
            least 10-15&nbsp;seconds.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7559"> </a>Lubricate the inner bearing internal race (A) with the recommended grease. Fit the ball race (B) on the steering shaft with
            the smaller diameter of the cage facing upwards, and grease the ball race. Insert the steering shaft into the steering tube,
            and push it in until it is axially seated.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_023503373.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_023903377.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7566"> </a>Fit the bottom yoke assembly to frame.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7568"> </a>Grease the ball race (B) and fit it to the upper outer ring (8) of the frame.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7570"> </a>Fit the inner race (A) of the upper bearing (6) to the steering head, with the larger diameter side of the race facing upwards.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7572"> </a>Install the sealing ring (5) with the flat side facing upwards.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7575"> </a>Tighten the adjuster ring nut (3) by hand until it seats against the seal (5).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7577"> </a>Fit special socket (C) no. 88713.1058 to the ring nut (3) and apply the torque wrench to the socket.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7579"> </a>Smear thread with recommended threadlocker and tighten adjuster ring nut (3) to 35 Nm ±5%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_013303378.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7585"> </a>Fit the steering head (2) on the ring nut (3), aligning the fork leg bores with the corresponding bores on the bottom yoke.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7587"> </a>Refit fork legs. Apply recommended grease to the screw (1).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7589"> </a>Tighten screw (1) on steering head to a torque of 18 Nm ±5%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_024003379.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7594"> </a>If removed, position splashguard (13) on bottom yoke (7) and fasten it by starting screws (14) with pre-applied recommended
            threadlocker and tightening them to 3 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_024103380.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7599"> </a>Refit the handlebar and U-bolts (<a href="78723.html#DUC91d0fef02b8c10058c8beb0d4d04214d">Refitting the handlebar</a>), Touring version.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7604"> </a>Refit the handlebar and U-bolts (<a href="78725.html#DUCb5769b802ba010058910ff90eb104e4d">Refitting the handlebar</a>), base and Pikes Peak versions.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7609"> </a>Refit the handlebar and U-bolts (<a href="80221.html#DUC681a8f902ba0100588f8ff90eb104e4d">Refitting the handlebar</a>), Granturismo version.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7614"> </a>Refit the headlight subframe (<a href="80875.html#DUC15e2c9d02b9c10058728d52e9edc2ad2">Refitting the rear subframe</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7619"> </a>Reinstall the front mudguard (<a href="78002.html#DUC7898aeb02a9c10058432b9f0263a2cd2">Refitting the front mudguard</a>) for the base version.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7624"> </a>Reinstall the front mudguard (<a href="78386.html#DUCd0ee77982a9c10058435b9f0263a2cd2">Refitting the front mudguard</a>) for Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7629"> </a>Refit the front brake callipers (<a href="78640.html#DUCe5522d382afb100587c48d91941052d2">Refitting the front brake system</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7634"> </a>Fill the braking system (<a href="77259.html#DUC4261033029fa1005800f816ce97b3fd2">Changing the front brake system fluid</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
